          The hate on Ronaldo is outrageous. Some people only want Ronaldo to be MOTM when he's scored 5 goals in a game. They can't allow themselves to see and appreciate his brilliance when he plays like a normal human being and scores only 1 very important opening goal against Celta Vigo away. A move that he started. He also started the move that resulted in Danilo's goal. He's off the ball movement is so effective and genius that it completely goes over most fans heads. Fans who claim to know football. These are the same people who praise Isco. Why? Because he touches the ball 10 times before releasing it, and he dribbles. 99% of those dribbles are useless. They slow down transitions, allow defenders to adjust etc. Ronaldo gets things done without the unnecessary dribbling and passing back and forth. Every move has a purpose. Of creating a chance or scoring a goal or winning a free kick or a corner. That is why he is rated higher.
